ul sadness is a myth. Sadness turns our features to clay, not porcelain.\n\n- David Levithan, Every Day\n|\nYou could get crickets to pop out of a book as a little, little girl, but now you have to relearn it? Well, children can do so many things until they're told they can't.\n\n- N.E. Bode, The Anybodies\n|\nThe worst grudge is being told that you are forgiven, yet your sins are still glowing in their hearts like a burning coal.\n\n- Michael\n|\neverything comes in time to him who knows how to wait . . . there is nothing stronger than these two: patience and time, they will do it all.\n\n- Leo Tolstoy, War and Peace\n|\nI've had so many bikini waxes, I cry every time I see a Popsicle stick.\n\n- Libba Bray, Beauty Queens\n|\n{...} It is hieroglyphic that will last, not stone heads. The future belongs to the word, not the image.(The mason Mutsose, in Achet-Aten).\n\n- Steven William Lawrie, Achet-Aten, or 1:1.618\n|\nJust as stars shine brightest in the darkest night, your joy blazes brilliantly through life’s problems when you count them as joy.\n\n- Elizabeth\n|\nIs there any courage, without craziness?\n\n- Lailah\n|\nTo change yourself, never forget to challenge yourself.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWe might not get to choose who we’re born as or where we come from, but only you can decide what becomes of you.\n\n- Reilyn J. Hardy, The Last Chronomancer\n|\nTo a lot of children, school is currently mostly a place to learn what you aren’t any good at.\n\n- Danny\n|\nThe courageous attitudes of leaders ramble around coward followers and sooner or later, they become courageous too!\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Leaders' Watchwords\n|\nThe more we know, the more we grief.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nOh God, let me not be cured of love, but let my passion grow! Let me love for love's sake!\n\n- Diane\n|\nDon't try to hurt anyone, you will not succeed because you can hurt only yourself.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nTaking actions will fulfill your dreams and wishes, not the prayers and blessings.\n\n- Ami